Joan Collins, 89, shared her delight at attending the prestigious Queen's Jubilee Pageant with a throwback video from the event. As footage showed her waving goodbye to Peppa Pig with a satin gloved hand, the actress enthused: "I can’t believe it’s already #flashbackfriday!" She continued: "I loved being in the #damesinjags for the Queens Platinum Jubilee procession … Such a spectacular thrilling event!" Some of her 277,000 followers praised her "flawless" look as she drove in an open-top car boasting a pale pink outfit paired with a matching veiled hat. She described the procession as "one of the most exciting days" of her life.